The former Chancellor and Tory leadership hopeful has described tackling illegal immigration as the “second emergency” his Government would tackle. He said he would do this by ensuring that those who arrive in the country illegally do not stay here, and by “[making] the Rwanda policy work”. But former Brexit MEP Ben Habib hit back, insisting illegal migrants arriving in the country at all demonstrated a border failure. He wrote in a post on Twitter: “Deporting people once they’re in the UK is not taking control of our borders. The control of our borders must take place at the border. In this case at entry into our territorial waters. It’s simple but it requires political will.” FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES...